Privacy Policy for EchoZen
Last updated: 2025‑04‑12

1. Introduction
EchoZen (“we”, “us”, “our”) provides live voice‑guided mindfulness sessions. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your data when you use our mobile app (“App”).

2. Information We Collect
Microphone Access

We request access to your device’s microphone only to enable live, real‑time voice sessions.

We do not record, store, or transmit your audio outside of the live session.

Analytics & Crash Reporting

We may collect anonymous usage data (screens visited, session length) via Firebase Analytics to improve the App.

Crash logs (no personal data) may be sent to our crash‑reporting service.

Purchases

We use RevenueCat to manage in‑app subscriptions and one‑time purchases. RevenueCat may collect your device identifiers and purchase receipts to validate entitlements.

3. How We Use Your Data
Microphone: To transmit audio during live sessions only.

Analytics: To understand feature usage and improve performance.

Purchases: To unlock premium content and manage subscriptions.

4. Third‑Party Services
Firebase (Google): Analytics, crash reporting, authentication, and data storage.

RevenueCat: In‑app purchase and subscription management.

We do not share your raw audio with any third party.

5. Data Retention & Security
We retain analytics data for up to 24 months, then delete it.

All data in transit is encrypted (HTTPS / TLS).

We follow industry‑standard security practices to protect your information.

6. Children’s Privacy
EchoZen is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from minors.

7. Your Rights
You can revoke microphone permission in your device settings (which will disable live sessions).

You can request deletion of your analytics data by contacting us (see below).

8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy occasionally. The “Last updated” date at the top will reflect changes.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or requests, email us at:
echozenappfirebase@gmail.com
